snippet.textDisplay: Personally I think that if an zombie outbreak reaches apocalypse level SOMETHING has got to be fueling it. Whether it be infected bugs, immunity to non-natural death (like can't be shot and killed sort of immunity),stupid fast speeds or stealth capabilities, something must fuel or else military and such can just destroy them like, *snap*, dead. But seriously it wouldn't just be a basic war against 100,000 or so units, it is possibly a couple 100 million or even a few BILLION zombies before enough data is obtained on them before a tactical attack is launched against them. And even THEN they won't stop at night to rest, and you'll mostly likely fail because of exhaustion or lack of resources like food/water or ammonation. Also look outside, how many houses do you see? They could have around 3 or 6 or maybe even more people in them and then finally think about hotels and apartments. Scared yet? You should because you only have one shot at this...
